    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "YOU. BETTER. WITH ALAN.\n\nAlan is building a vertically integrated health partner that unites insurance and smart healthcare delivery into one seamless system. Our vision is to make prevention the new norm of care for all.\n\nOur mission: Help people live in good health to 100 while helping employers feel proud, turning health benefits from a cost centre into their most valuable investment.\n\nBy connecting all aspects of care (private, public, and direct to consumer) we create the most member-centric healthcare experience, reducing claims costs while generating new monetization opportunities.\n\nWe partner with tens of thousands of companies across France 🇫🇷, Spain 🇪🇸, Belgium 🇧🇪, and Canada 🇨🇦, serving over a million members.\n\n\nHOW WE WORK: OUR LEADERSHIP PRINCIPLES\n\n - Mission is the Boss — We think long-term and are methodical optimists who take risks, seeking our mission's success above all else.\n\n - Distributed Ownership — Accountable enlightened despots: everyone owns their decisions and results.\n\n - Radical Transparency — All information is accessible and written-first, so everyone can make the best decisions asynchronously.\n\n - Always Growing — Direct, positive, and caring feedback, combined with self-growth ownership.\n\n\n⭐ MAKE A TANGIBLE IMPACT EVERY DAY\n\nWhen companies choose Alan, HR teams are the ones making it happen: enrolling employees, managing payroll contributions, and handling billing. Our mission is to make these processes frictionless, reliable, and even delightful.\n\nAs a Software Engineer on this team, you will:\n\n - Engineer our employee affiliation engine: reliably process thousands of lifecycle events daily.\n\n - Simplify payroll and billing: craft tools that HR teams love 💙.\n\n - Build seamless integrations: connect with platforms like Payfit and Workday so things “just work.”\n\n - Automate workflows at scale: adapt solutions to companies of all sizes across multiple countries.\n\n - Make billing delightful: ensure invoices are accurate, reliable, and easy to manage.\n\n - Collaborate across teams: partner with product, design, and ops to deliver a unified experience.\n\n\nWHY THIS ROLE IS SPECIAL:\n\n - Work on mission-critical systems powering Alan’s growth and renewals.\n\n - Impact hundreds of thousands of lives, making it simple for companies to use Alan.\n\n - Solve complex business and technical puzzles, while maintaining our “uncompromising simplicity” principle.\n\n - Shape product direction and experience, not just ship code.\n\n - Join a team obsessed with engineering excellence and continuous learning.\n\n\n🛠 YOUR PLAYGROUND\n\n - Stack: Python/Flask, React, React Native, PostgreSQL.\n\n - What you’ll do: ship solutions that handle high complexity and scale across multiple countries, collaborating closely with product and design teams.\n\n - Impact: your work touches core business operations and enables hundreds of thousands of employees to benefit from Alan every day.\n\n\n👥 WHO WE’RE LOOKING FOR\n\n - We are looking for software engineers of all experience levels, ideally with backend and full-stack experience.\n\n - Comfortable digging into complex business logic, especially around insurance and payroll.\n\n - Passionate about turning complex processes into simple, elegant solutions.\n\n - Experienced in building scalable systems that handle real-world complexity.\n\n - B2B experience is a plus!\n\n - Well-versed in OOP languages (Python, Java, C#) and excited about modern web technologies (JavaScript).\n\n - Fluent in English (French is a plus but not required).\n\n - Curious, self-starting, humble, collaborative, and eager to grow.\n\n\n🙌 PERKS \u0026 BENEFITS\n\n - Fair rewards \u0026 equity packages.\n\n - Flexible office \u0026 remote options.\n\n - Top-tier equipment: MacBook Pro, monitor, noise-canceling headphones.\n\n - Flexible vacation \u0026 hours.\n\n - Comprehensive healthcare for you, children, and partners.\n\n - Transport support and coaching for personal growth.\n\n - Training budget for conferences, courses, books.\n\n - Extended parental leave for all parents.\n\n\n🔄 RECRUITMENT NOTE\n\n - You may ultimately join the part of the engineering organization where you can have the most impact.\n\n - We hire people, not roles. Don’t worry if you don’t check every box — high potential and curiosity matter most.\n\n🔖 Check out our About Alan https://alan.com/about and Career https://alan.com/careers pages, as well as our Medium https://medium.com/alan, blog https://blog.alan.com/ and Glassdoor page https://www.glassdoor.com/Overview/Working-at-Alan-EI_IE1696043.11,15.htm for more info.\n\n🔄 A quick note about the process\nNote: While you're applying for a specific area,, you may join a different engineering team based on where we think you'll have the most impact. Check out descriptions of other areas here https://www.notion.so/alaninsurance/Software-Engineering-Areas-Alan-2c61426e8be7805bacd2cdbc08c32640?source=copy_link.",
